		<h4><div>Victoria Symphony&rsquo;s Tania Miller<br>&amp; guitarist Sharon Isbin</div></h4>
		<p>The widely-recorded American classical guitarist Sharon Isbin has performed just about everywhere, including at the White House and at Ground Zero, and now she will finally perform with the MCO!</p>
		<p>Isbin&rsquo;s acclaim is legendary. One small resum&eacute; item: in 1989, she founded the Juilliard School guitar department! Anne Manson: &ldquo;This is a chance to hear at last this venerated guitarist, who has had a celebrated international career for years, in a huge range of repertoire.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>Victoria Symphony&rsquo;s Tania Miller has also been on our wish list for some time. The charismatic conductor has transformed that orchestra into a &ldquo;technically superior instrument&rdquo; since taking the reins there 11 seasons ago. She&rsquo;ll love the MCO!</p>
		<p><b>Tania Miller</b></p>
		<p>The repertoire for this concert is wildly varied &mdash; everything from guitar transcriptions of baroque works to contemporary pieces, even <i>Billy&rsquo;s Theme</i> from <i>The Departed</i> &mdash; all of which will be no problem for Tania Miller.</p>
		<p>Miller has a deep belief in expanding the repertoire, and has commissioned works from DJs, rap artists, Japanese percussionists and First Nations singers to perform with the Victoria Symphony.</p>
		<p>&ldquo;Her impresario&rsquo;s approach draws freely from the world around her.&rdquo; &mdash; <i>Ottawa Citizen</i></p>

